# Module 3 Project: Password Generator

## User Story and Acceptance Criteria
User Story
AS AN employee with access to sensitive data
I WANT to randomly generate a password that meets certain criteria
SO THAT I can create a strong password that provides greater security

Acceptance Criteria
GIVEN I need a new, secure password
WHEN I click the button to generate a password
THEN I am presented with a series of prompts for password criteria

WHEN prompted for password criteria
THEN I select which criteria to include in the password

WHEN prompted for the length of the password
THEN I choose a length of at least 8 characters and no more than 128 characters

WHEN asked for character types to include in the password
THEN I confirm whether or not to include lowercase, uppercase, numeric, and/or special characters

WHEN I answer each prompt
THEN my input should be validated and at least one character type should be selected

WHEN all prompts are answered
THEN a password is generated that matches the selected criteria

WHEN the password is generated
THEN the password is either displayed in an alert or written to the page

## Description
I went rogue on this one; after I cloned the starter code, I wasn't sure where or how to get started. 

I was wanting to access the lecture recordings to freshen up on some of the topics (arrays,functions, objects, etc) so I could build out the JS file, but I couldn't access the recordings on bootcampspot for some reason.

Option B was trying to find youtube lectures on JS, other examples, to then apply to the started code given on bootcampspot.  After starting the video, I liked the look and functionality of the other password generator a lot more. I decided to code along with the video as the JS file was written out, and since I was understanding what was going on in the video (and unable to access lecture videos), I decided to just make this my project and adjust later if possible.

The creator of this password generator is someone named Florin Pop.
