## Why I Went Rogue
I thought walking along with this video was useful for a couple reasons:
    A. I can't put my finger on it yet, but the way this guy develops a JS script feels a little different that the way Andre (our instructor) does.

    B. The way Florin writes this JS script seems to be very efficient.  There are a lot of instructions building a lot of functionality, but written in not that many lines of code.

    C. It was useful to see how the developer decomposed the project into parts:
        1. Generator Functions - writing generator functions to generate random password inputs
        2. Writing DOM elements, equivalent variables to be used by DOM elements
        3. Generate Password Function - passing the above into a password generation function that uses and         combines the above elements to generate an actual password.
        4.

    D.


## Current Problems with Application and Assignment
